            <div class="phase-header">Combining Like Terms</div>
            <div class="time-estimate">‚è± 8 MINUTES</div>
            
            <div class="lesson-chunk">
                Sir, like terms have the same variables raised to the same powers. Combine them by adding or subtracting their coefficients. 
            </div>
            
            <div class="example-box">
                <strong>EXAMPLE:</strong>
                <br>Simplify: 3x + 5y - x + 2y
                <br><em>Combine x terms: (3x - x) = 2x</em>
                <br><em>Combine y terms: (5y + 2y) = 7y</em>
                <br><em>Result: 2x + 7y</em>
            </div>
            
