            <div class="time-estimate">‚è± 8 MINUTES</div>
            
            <div class="lesson-chunk">
                Sir, use the distributive property to multiply a term by an expression inside parentheses.
                <br>$a(b + c) = ab + ac$
            </div>
            
            <div class="example-box">
                <strong>EXAMPLE:</strong>
                <br>Simplify: 4(2x - 3)
                <br><em>Distribute 4: (4 * 2x) - (4 * 3)</em>
                <br><em>Result: 8x - 12</em>
            </div>
            
            <div class="critical-principle">
                Watch for negative signs when distributing! They apply to all terms inside.
            </div>
            
